{
  "id": "S2R2M530",
  "title": {
    "product_var": "ZPRODTSK",
    "text": "EDIT PRIMARY COMMAND - STATS",
    "version_var": "ZSHRTVER",
    "prefix": "HELP"
  },
  "type": "menu",
  "body": {
    "rows": [
      {
        "type": "command",
        "variable": "ZCMD"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Purpose"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "The STATS command will generate statistics (level stamping) when"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "standard numbering is on."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Format"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "STATS  [ON ]"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "[OFF]"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Remarks"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "When STATS is on and line numbering is standard (STD), columns 79"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "and 80 contain a level number."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "Each time that SPF/PC starts editing such a file, it finds the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "largest level number and adds one to it. Unless this number is"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "overridden by a LEVEL command, it places this new number in the"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "level number field of any record that is changed or inserted."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "By using this, you can tell which records have been updated and"
      },
      {
        "type": "text",
        "content": "relatively when the update took place."
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "blank"
      },
      {
        "type": "field_row",
        "fields": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "(Hit"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "content": "ENTER+to return to previous menu)"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
